<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-14T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-14T04:00:00-05:00" n="864" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d864">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/1083: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Tenney</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-14T17:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">April 14,
                                        1920—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 14—11:52
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>80. Referring to the Department’s telegram of April 8, 3 p.m. I am unable
                            to ascertain facts regarding unofficial negotiations between Chinese and
                            Japanese regarding Shantung settlement. The Minister for Foreign Affairs
                            denies that direct negotiations are proceeding, or are contemplated by
                            the Chinese Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Tenney</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>